messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /api/orders

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  false

- HEAD:
  false

- POST:
  true

- OPTIONS:
  false

- TRACE:
  false

- GET:
  true

- PUT:
  false

- DELETE:
  false

- PATCH:
  false

Explanation:
- In server.js the order router is mounted with app.use('/api/orders', orderRoutes); so all routes defined in routes/orderRoutes.js are prefixed with /api/orders.
- In routes/orderRoutes.js the root route for that router is router.route('/').post(protect, addOrderItems).get(protect, admin, getOrders); therefore:
  - POST /api/orders is explicitly defined and handled by addOrderItems (with the protect middleware). So POST is allowed.
  - GET /api/orders is explicitly defined and handled by getOrders (with protect and admin). So GET is allowed.
- There are no explicit handlers in the code for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, nor any router/app-wide all/any handler that would accept all methods. Per the instruction to base answers only on the code (not on framework default behavior), those methods are marked false.
- "All HTTP methods acceptable" is false because there is no code allowing every method (no app.all/router.all or similar).
